                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2) wish there few remarks which you see are candid on<lb/> my part—let me notice in\n                the first instance, that<lb/> up to the present Hour I cannot unravel the<lb/>\n                mystery why you should have so inveterate an<lb/> objection to me. I often ask\n                myself the question<lb/> what can the reason be? I have never harmed<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Leeser</persName>, nor have I thought I could do so—<lb/> In looking at\n                your letter to me of <date>Sept 5612</date> which<lb/> breathes a spirit of kindness\n                and good feeling, and<lb/> the amicable disposition with which we met each<lb/> at\n                the <add>חנוך</add> at <placeName>Syracuse</placeName>, where I officiated as<lb/>\n                <add>חזן</add>\n                <persName>Dr Raphale</persName> preached—I cannot but be<lb/> astonished at the\n                Report you spread of me when<lb/> I met you at <placeName>Charleston</placeName> in\n                the following Winter<lb/> when that Report reached me, knowing that I care<lb/> defy\n                the whole world as to my character of the<lb/> truth be adhered to I lost no time in\n                sending<lb/> without delay to <placeName>Europe</placeName> all that you said of\n                me<lb/> in the name of <persName>Dr Raphale</persName> and by the next<lb/> mail I\n                received a Document from the <add>בית דין</add><lb/> of\n                    <placeName>London</placeName> proving at once all such Reports to<lb/> be\n                false—and while yet at <placeName>Charleston</placeName> I wrote to<lb/>\n                <persName>Dr Raphale</persName> calling upon him to state which<lb/> he know of me,\n                and to say why He did report<lb/> those things which you said came from him<lb/>\n                copy of the said letter was handed over to <persName>Mr<lb/> Hart</persName> the\n                    <add>פרנס</add> of the <add>קהלה</add> there—but he deigned not<lb/> to answer\n                it. I wrote a second—and the result<lb/> was the same—I wrote a third in which I</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
