                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">(3</p>\n            <p>used <add>דברים קשים</add> and this ended in a reply written<lb/> in Hebrew\n                throughout of an evasive character<lb/> and flatly denying any thing ever having\n                been<lb/> said by him to any one—now I ask you what<lb/> is all this from men who\n                are placed at the<lb/> Head of Congregations to level <sic>there</sic> Religion<lb/>\n                and Moralists—who am I to believe?—<lb/> the letter I have in my possession which\n                you<lb/> can have whenever you please—copies of all<lb/> the letters and Documents I\n                sent to <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> Letters to and fro passed between us\n                but were<lb/> unsatisfactory in their result—</p>\n            <p>Many many persons here in this City and in<lb/>\n                <placeName>Syracuse</placeName> urged me to indict you for <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >slander</hi><lb/> in order to ascertain who was the real author<lb/> of the\n                Report—I would not—for state litigation<lb/> especially between the Clergy—we are\n                low enough<lb/> already and for the love of my Religion I would<lb/> not be led on\n                to such a course. I had hoped<lb/> to have been in a position long ere this to<lb/>\n                have learned who was the aggressor in this<lb/> matter. Having met you here on some\n                    <sic>occasins</sic><lb/> I feign would have asked you, but my Head<lb/> told me\n                    <add>הרחק משכן רע</add> for such I held you, &amp;<lb/> you could not blame me,\n                for when I reflect that<lb/> you had no feeling for an innocent man, who<lb/> had a\n                large family to support, and by your<lb/> villainous Report I might have starved\n                with them</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
