                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">(4</p>\n            <p>Had not the God of <placeName>Israel</placeName> been to me <add>לעזר</add><lb/>\n                truly did I say with the sweet Psalmist of<lb/>\n                <placeName>Israel</placeName>\n                <add>ה' לי לא אירא, מה יעשה לי אדם</add><lb/> In spite of all my enemies, I have\n                proved to the<lb/> American Jews that I am what I represent myself<lb/> to be a true\n                Orthodox Israelite, capable of filling<lb/> any office to which I may be\n                appointed—and I<lb/> can without fear challenge any of the Ministers<lb/> throughout\n                the <placeName>United States</placeName> in point of ability<lb/> and Competency for\n                a Jewish Divine—and they<lb/> are now satisfied beyond doubt—that all those<lb/> who\n                attempted to <sic>injured</sic> me are none else<lb/> but <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >Mountebanks</hi> and <hi rend=\"underline\">Hypocrites</hi> do not my<lb/> friend\n                think me harsh but “<add>אמת יורה דרכו</add>”<lb/> Now I ask you is it not due to\n                me, that<lb/> you should give me up your author of<lb/> the Report you spread about\n                me at <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> you said there it was <persName>Dr\n                    Raphale</persName>. He denies<lb/> it, and when he was asked about me two<lb/>\n                years since when I had a call to this City<lb/> His reply was, Report speaks\n                    to<add>?</add> of me, and<lb/> you knew all about it. but I believe that<lb/> He\n                himself was the calumniator, for I have<lb/> had reason to think so since that\n                time—and when<lb/> I wrote to <persName>Mr Sevien</persName> of\n                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, He stated He<lb/> was sure you would make the\n                    <sic>amende</sic> Honorable<lb/> if you were the aggressor. Now if you are</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
