                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/manifest/annotation/p5",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">(5</p>\n            <p>not the guilty party why you should still be<lb/> thought so by me <add>לך בדרך הישר\n                    ועשה הטוב, אמת ומשפט עשה בין ארץ לחבירו, ולא תגור מפני</add><lb/><add>איש כי\n                    המשפט לאלהים הוא, והוא יבקש את נרדף</add><lb/><add>ה' ישלם לך פעלך והיית נקי פה\n                    ומישראל</add><lb/> I have no desire to make any public use of it<lb/> but I am\n                anxious to know the Truth for I<lb/> have never since that time spoken to\n                    <persName>Dr Raphale</persName><lb/> for I hold it dangerous until I am set\n                to<lb/> right in the matter. I must not omit the<lb/> Circumstance you witnessed at\n                    <placeName>Syracuse</placeName> at<lb/> the festival where the Dr spoke of me in\n                such<lb/> commendable terms—I know you stated this<lb/> at\n                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>—but you should first have<lb/> asked me, and I\n                could have assured you to<lb/> the contrary—again I have a letter in my<lb/>\n                possession sent by the Dr to <placeName>Louisville</placeName> in my<lb/> behalf\n                which contradicts all he said to you<lb/> about me—Now I leave the matter in<lb/>\n                your hands whether you think we should<lb/> remain open and severe enemies for<lb/>\n                life, or whether you will do me the justice to<lb/> set the matter at issue by\n                declaring to me<lb/> the truth throughout <add>אני שלום וכי אדבר המה\n                    מלחמה</add><lb/>—<add>אם לא יגיד ונשא עוני</add><lb/> I shall be willing to\n                return you any favor<lb/> you may desire of me as far as I am able<lb/> in my public\n                capacity—my whole time is<lb/> devoted for the benefit of my people—you no\n                doubt<lb/> read the Asmonean, and see my articles</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8jc31/canvas/p5"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
